through the whole "I respect you/Angelo",
etc. I told him that I felt it was necessary
to make sure we were communicating
since we had not in a while. As such, I
informed him we sent a termination letter
last November due to their breaches,
which makes us feel we now have no
obligation to support their merchants. I
said we are being forced to move their ~2k
merchants to the gateway product that is
powered by authorize.net as a result of
the acquisition. I told him that if this
transition is going to create problems for
them, they can go back to that
termination letter and correct the
breaches at which time we would provide
them additional time.
